page: List of U.S. state constitutional provisions allowing self-representation in state courts
message: South Carolina Code Ann. Sec. 40-5-80 was amended in 2002 to prohibit non-lawyers from representing someone pro bono.  I changed the quotation and the source to reflect current state law.
